HEX ()
It decodes a decimal-encoded hexadecimal field.


||
it is a string concatenation (una dietro l'altra) 
in sqlite and postgres is an infix operator 

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~


INDEX		it is used as reference for the database.
		it has the same value of an index in a book

constraints	they are used to specify rules for data in a table. 
		they can be specified when the table is created (CREATE TABLE)or after the table is created (ALTER TABLE)

CONTRAINTS ON SQL:
NOT NULL	a column cannot store NULL value
UNIQUE		each row for a column must have an unique value
PRIMATY KEY	it is NOT NULL and UNIQUE. ensure that a column has unique values
FOREIN KEY	it is used to match values in another table
CHECK		ensures that values in a column meets a specific condition
DEFAULT		specifies a default value for a column


transactions
